Title: N=2 Superintegrable f-Toda Mapping and Super-NLS Hierarchy in the (1|2)
  Superspace
Authors: V.B. Derjagin, A.N. Leznov and A.S. Sorin
Comments: 11 pages, latex, no figures, some misprints corrected
Report-no: JINR E2-96-410
Journal-ref: Phys.Atom.Nucl. 61 (1998) 1990-1996; Yad.Fiz. 61 (1998) 2097-2103
\\
  A new integrable N=2 supersymmetric f-Toda mapping in (1|2) superspace,
acting like the symmetry transformation of N=2 supersymmetric NLS hierarchy, is
proposed. The first two Hamiltonian structures and the recursion operator
connecting all evolution systems and Hamiltonian structures of the N=2
super-NLS hierarchy are constructed in explicit form using only invariance
conditions with respect to the f-Toda mapping. A new representation for its
Hamiltonians is observed.
